      • forName

        protected java.lang.Object forName(java.lang.String prefix,
                                   java.lang.Class cls,
                                   java.lang.String classname,
                                   java.lang.String[] options)
                            throws java.lang.Exception
        Tries to instantiate a new instance of the given class and checks whether it is an instance of the specified class. For convenience one can also specify a classname prefix (e.g., "weka.classifiers") to avoid long classnames and then instantiate it with the shortened classname (e.g., "trees.J48").
        Parameters:
        prefix - the classname prefix (without trailing dot)
        cls - the class to check whether the generated object is an instance of
        classname - the classname to instantiate
        options - optional options for the object
        Returns:
        the configured object
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if instantiation fails
